The paper proposes a new model for graph-based semi-supervised learning using graph convolutional neural networks and Gaussian processes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms for learning from data. The paper also involves neural networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses graph-based data, which is often studied in the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
